  <p>Preventative care is the foundation of your pet's long-term health. Regular checkups and vaccinations can catch problems early and help your pet live a longer, healthier life.</p>

  <h2>Vaccinations and Disease Prevention</h2>
  <p>We use only the safest and most effective vaccines, tailored to meet each pet's individual needs. Our vaccination protocols are based on current veterinary guidelines and your pet's specific lifestyle and risk factors.</p>

  <h3>Our Preventative Care Services</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Annual wellness examinations</li>
    <li>Core and lifestyle vaccinations</li>
    <li>Parasite prevention (flea, tick, heartworm)</li>
    <li>Early disease detection through screening tests</li>
    <li>Senior pet wellness programs</li>
    <li>Puppy and kitten care packages</li>
  </ul>

  <h3>Why Preventative Care Matters</h3>
  <p>Many health problems in pets develop gradually and can be difficult to detect without regular examinations. Annual or semi-annual wellness visits give us the chance to monitor your pet's health, catch potential issues early, and adjust their care plan as they age.</p>

  <p>Contact us to schedule a wellness exam for your pet.</p>
